body:
Hi! thank you for great software!!

I encountered an internal error when assigning to an array of structs.
This issue does not occur in version 5.026 (a downgraded version of Fedora).

```systemverilog
module tb_top();
    logic clk;
    logic n;
    top top(.n, .clk);
    initial begin
        clk = 0;
        $display("n = %d", n);
        #100;
        $finish;
    end
endmodule

module top (
    input logic clk,
    output logic n
);
    localparam int N = 2;
    typedef struct {
        logic valid;
    } hoge_t;
    hoge_t hoge[N];

    for (genvar i = 0; i < N; i++) begin
        always_ff @(posedge clk) begin
            hoge[i].valid <= 0;
        end
    end
    always_comb begin
        n = hoge[0].valid;
    end
endmodule
```

What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?
```
% verilator tb_top.sv --cc --timing        
%Error: Internal Error: tb_top.sv:25:21: ../V3Delayed.cpp:344: Malformed LHS in NBA
   25 |             hoge[i].valid <= 0;
      |                     ^~~~~
                        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html for more assistance.
```

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?
```
% verilator --version              
Verilator 5.030 2024-10-27 rev fedora-5.030
```


What OS and distribution are you using?
fedora

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?
